ml=0|pssc=0 }} &lt;/table> |Dockbay= }} {{Infobox close}} ==Overview== The Fujin can carry M-class cargo and hence the [[Triplex Scanner]], making it along with the [[Discoverer]] and [[Kestrel]] one of the better scout craft. ==Background== The Yaki developed this small, fast, and maneuverable scout to keep an eye on the outer reaches of their sectors and to accompany raiding parties venturing into other sectors. ==Variants== ===Fujin=== {{regular}} ===Fujin Raider=== {{raider}} ===Fujin Sentinel=== {{sentinel}} The Fujin Sentinel, however, is often considered to be the best variant, being the fastest and best in all other stats, besides cargo capacity (which is still quite adequate), and the negligible M5 hull strength. ==Physical Characteristics== == Combat == Scout ships like the Fujin are too weak to fare well in dogfights. However, the Fujin is one of only three ships in its class to carry the [[Silkworm Missile]] and [[Remote Guided Warhead|RGW]]; this makes it surprisingly dangerous to [[M4|interceptors]], [[M3|heavy fighters]], and even [[M6|corvettes]] as it can destroy them with a few salvos. == Equipment == {| |+ '''Missiles''' |- style="vertical-align:top;" | *[[Mosquito Missile]] *[[Wasp Missile]] *[[Dragonfly Missile]] | *[[Silkworm Missile]] *[[Disruptor Missile]] *[[Firefly Missile]] | *[[Hurricane Missile]] *[[Aurora Missile]] *[[Remote Guided Warhead]] | *[[Rapier Missile]] *[[Firelance Missile]] *[[Wildfire Missile]] |} == Availability == The Fujin can be bought at the Yaki Shipyard in [[Senator's Badlands]]. == Suggested Roles== The Fujin Sentinel is both one of the fastest and best shielded variants of the Fujin. This makes it extremely hard to kill and an effective distraction, as well as packing a punch with PACs, letting it kill off enemy M5s. == See Also== {{M5}} {{M5category}} {{Yaki Navbox}}